## 1. Purpose
This policy establishes [COMPANY]'s security and privacy awareness and training program, ensuring every workforce member understands their responsibilities for protecting information — especially PHI — and can recognize and respond to threats such as phishing. A trained workforce is [COMPANY]'s most important control against social engineering and human error.

## 2. Scope
This policy applies to all workforce members (employees, contractors, interns, temporary staff) and any third-party personnel with access to [COMPANY] systems, [AWS]/[Snowflake]/[GitHub] environments, or PHI. Role-based training additionally applies to engineering, support, and any role with elevated access or direct PHI handling.

## 3. Policy
1. All workforce members **shall** complete security and privacy awareness training **at hire** (before or within [N — e.g. 30] days of being granted access) and **at least annually** thereafter (HIPAA requirement).
2. Training **shall** cover HIPAA Privacy and Security basics, PHI handling, acceptable use, password/MFA hygiene, phishing and social engineering, incident reporting, and clean desk/clear screen.
3. [COMPANY] **shall** conduct **phishing simulations** at least [quarterly]; repeat clickers receive additional training per §6.
4. Personnel in high-risk or specialized roles **shall** complete **role-based training** appropriate to their duties (§5).
5. Workforce members **shall** receive **ad hoc security reminders/updates** when significant new threats or policy changes arise (HIPAA security reminders).
6. **Completion of all training shall be tracked and recorded**, and records retained per §8.
7. Access to PHI or production systems **may** be suspended for workforce members who do not complete required training by the deadline.

## 4. Training Content
The general awareness curriculum **shall** include at minimum:
- HIPAA Privacy and Security Rule fundamentals and the minimum-necessary principle.
- Identifying and handling PHI; permitted uses and disclosures.
- Password and MFA practices; protection against malicious software (HIPAA).
- Recognizing phishing, social engineering, and suspicious activity.
- How and when to report a security incident or suspected breach (links to `../resilience/incident-response-plan.md.template`).
- Acceptable use, clean desk / clear screen, and physical security (links to `hr-security-policy.md.template` and `physical-and-environmental-security-policy.md.template`).

## 5. Role-Based Training
| Role | Additional Training |
|---|---|
| Engineering / DevOps | Secure coding, secrets management, [AWS]/[Snowflake]/[GitHub] security, secure SDLC. |
| Customer Support | PHI handling in support workflows, identity verification, minimum necessary. |
| Privileged/Admin users | Least privilege, break-glass procedures, change management. |
| Incident responders | IR plan, runbooks, tabletop participation. |
| New people-managers | Sanctions process, reporting obligations. |

## 6. Phishing Simulations
[COMPANY] runs simulated phishing campaigns at least [quarterly] using [phishing platform]. Results are tracked; workforce members who fail a simulation receive remedial training, and repeat failures are escalated to their manager and may trigger additional measures per `hr-security-policy.md.template`. Simulation metrics (click rate, report rate) are reported to management review.

## 7. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [Security Officer / CISO] | Owns the program; defines curriculum; reviews metrics. |
| [Privacy Officer] | Ensures HIPAA privacy content is current and complete. |
| [HR / People Ops] | Enrolls new hires; enforces completion; integrates with onboarding. |
| Managers | Ensure their teams complete training on time; reinforce expectations. |
| All Workforce | Complete assigned training by the deadline; apply it; report incidents. |

See `../governance/roles-and-responsibilities.md.template` for full role definitions.

## 8. Records & Completion Tracking
Training assignments, completion dates, scores, and phishing-simulation results **shall** be recorded in [LMS / training platform] and retained for at least **six (6) years** to satisfy HIPAA documentation requirements (45 CFR § 164.316(b)(2)). Records are produced as evidence during audits and HITRUST assessment.

## 9. Exceptions
Exceptions to this policy require documented risk acceptance per `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by the [Security Officer], time-bound, and recorded in the exceptions log. The annual-training requirement is regulatory and should not be excepted.

## 10. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
Compliance is measured through training completion rates, on-time completion, and phishing-simulation performance, reported to management review (`../governance/management-review.md.template`). Failure to complete required training is a policy violation handled per `hr-security-policy.md.template`, including the HIPAA workforce sanctions process (`../healthcare/sanctions-policy.md.template`).

